    en: "Many legal documents require notarization — a notary public verifies the signer's identity and witnesses the signature. In New York, notary fees are capped at $2 per signature by law. Many banks, libraries, UPS stores, and government offices offer notarization — some for free. Remote online notarization is now also available in New York. Knowing where to go and what to bring saves time and money."
